Ri referred to a joint statement issued by Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump at the first-ever summit between a sitting US president and a North Korean leader in Singapore on 12 June, when Kim pledged to work towards the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula while Trump pledged to guarantee North Korea's security.
North Korea was seeking a formal end to the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States said Pyongyang must first give up its nuclear weapons.
