The culture of pride in staying up all night studying still exists, he said, adding that modern technology and the increasing pressure on students meant that lack of sleep was a growing problem.
Ensuring adequate, good quality sleep should be a student's secret weapon to combat stress, fatigue and anxiety, he said - also to avoid weight gain, as lack of sleep puts the brain in a hungry mode, making them hungry all the time.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old student from California, studying chemistry and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler design the course, after attending one of his classes last year during his first year at Harvard.
He said that the course opened his eyes and inspired him to press for a campus-wide course.
